   documentation, user-interface materials, system architecture,
   configuration files, application programming interfaces, and related
   materials, to the extent protected by applicable law.

b. “Institutional Implementation” means a version of the Platform that
   is configured, branded, customized, deployed, or maintained for a
   particular school, university, organization, or other institution.

c. “Institution-Specific Addendum” means a separate written agreement
   granting a named institution permission to use a particular
   Institutional Implementation.

d. “Copyright Owner” or “Licensor” means Angelo Pambid Peralta, unless
   ownership is modified by a separate valid written agreement.

e. “Authorized Institution” means an institution specifically named in
   a valid Institution-Specific Addendum.

f. “Authorized User” means an employee, officer, faculty member,
   administrator, student, contractor, or other person authorized to
   access an Institutional Implementation solely for the Authorized
   Institution’s approved internal operations.

